Package: iviRA
Type: Package
Title: The IVI-RA model
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jeroen P.", "Jansen", , "jeroen.jansen@thevalueinitiative.org", c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Devin", "Incerti", , "devin.incerti@thevalueinitiative.org", role = "aut")
    )
Maintainer: <jeroen.jansen@thevalueinitiative.org>
Description: An R package for running the IVI-RA model, an individual patient simulation that
    simulates the costs, health outcomes, and risks associated with disease-modifying anti-rheumatic 
    drugs (DMARDs) and biologic DMARDSs (bDMARDs) for patients with moderate to severe 
    rheumatoid arthritis.
URL: https://github.com/InnovationValueInitiative/IVI-RA
BugReports: https://github.com/InnovationValueInitiative/IVI-RA/issues
License: GPL-3
LazyData: TRUE
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
LinkingTo: Rcpp, 
           RcppArmadillo, 
           hesim
Imports:
    data.table,
    hesim,
    MASS,
    msm,
    Rcpp,
    tmvtnorm
Suggests:
    covr,
    flexsurv,
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
SystemRequirements: C++11
